4100  /// Return the newly negated expression if the cost is not expensive and
4101  /// set the cost in \p Cost to indicate that if it is cheaper or neutral to
4102  /// do the negation.
4103  virtual SDValue getNegatedExpression(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4104  bool LegalOps, bool OptForSize,
4105  NegatibleCost &Cost,
4106  unsigned Depth = 0) const;
4107 
4108  SDValue getCheaperOrNeutralNegatedExpression(
4109  SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, bool LegalOps, bool OptForSize,
4110  const NegatibleCost CostThreshold = NegatibleCost::Neutral,
4111  unsigned Depth = 0) const {
4112  NegatibleCost Cost = NegatibleCost::Expensive;
4113  SDValue Neg =
4114  getNegatedExpression(Op, DAG, LegalOps, OptForSize, Cost, Depth);
4115  if (!Neg)
4116  return SDValue();
4117 
4118  if (Cost <= CostThreshold)
4119  return Neg;
4120 
4121  // Remove the new created node to avoid the side effect to the DAG.
4122  if (Neg->use_empty())
4123  DAG.RemoveDeadNode(Neg.getNode());
4124  return SDValue();
4125  }
4126 
4127  /// This is the helper function to return the newly negated expression only
4128  /// when the cost is cheaper.
4129  SDValue getCheaperNegatedExpression(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4130  bool LegalOps, bool OptForSize,
4131  unsigned Depth = 0) const {
4132  return getCheaperOrNeutralNegatedExpression(Op, DAG, LegalOps, OptForSize,
4133  NegatibleCost::Cheaper, Depth);
4134  }
4135 
4136  /// This is the helper function to return the newly negated expression if
4137  /// the cost is not expensive.
4138  SDValue getNegatedExpression(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG, bool LegalOps,
4139  bool OptForSize, unsigned Depth = 0) const {
4140  NegatibleCost Cost = NegatibleCost::Expensive;
4141  return getNegatedExpression(Op, DAG, LegalOps, OptForSize, Cost, Depth);
4142  }

4290  NumFixedArgs = FTy->getNumParams();
4291  Args = std::move(ArgsList);
4292 
4293  CB = &Call;
4294 
4295  return *this;

4525  /// This callback is used to prepare for a volatile or atomic load.
4526  /// It takes a chain node as input and returns the chain for the load itself.
4527  ///
4528  /// Having a callback like this is necessary for targets like SystemZ,
4529  /// which allows a CPU to reuse the result of a previous load indefinitely,
4530  /// even if a cache-coherent store is performed by another CPU. The default
4531  /// implementation does nothing.
4532  virtual SDValue prepareVolatileOrAtomicLoad(SDValue Chain, const SDLoc &DL,
4533  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4534  return Chain;
4535  }

4537  /// Should SelectionDAG lower an atomic store of the given kind as a normal
4538  /// StoreSDNode (as opposed to an AtomicSDNode)? NOTE: The intention is to
4539  /// eventually migrate all targets to the using StoreSDNodes, but porting is
4540  /// being done target at a time.
4541  virtual bool lowerAtomicStoreAsStoreSDNode(const StoreInst &SI) const {
4542  assert(SI.isAtomic() && "violated precondition");
4543  return false;
4544  }
4545 
4546  /// Should SelectionDAG lower an atomic load of the given kind as a normal
4547  /// LoadSDNode (as opposed to an AtomicSDNode)? NOTE: The intention is to
4548  /// eventually migrate all targets to the using LoadSDNodes, but porting is
4549  /// being done target at a time.
4550  virtual bool lowerAtomicLoadAsLoadSDNode(const LoadInst &LI) const {
4551  assert(LI.isAtomic() && "violated precondition");
4552  return false;
4553  }

4556  /// This callback is invoked by the type legalizer to legalize nodes with an
4557  /// illegal operand type but legal result types. It replaces the
4558  /// LowerOperation callback in the type Legalizer. The reason we can not do
4559  /// away with LowerOperation entirely is that LegalizeDAG isn't yet ready to
4560  /// use this callback.
4561  ///
4562  /// TODO: Consider merging with ReplaceNodeResults.
4563  ///
4564  /// The target places new result values for the node in Results (their number
4565  /// and types must exactly match those of the original return values of
4566  /// the node), or leaves Results empty, which indicates that the node is not
4567  /// to be custom lowered after all.
4568  /// The default implementation calls LowerOperation.
4569  virtual void LowerOperationWrapper(SDNode *N,
4570  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
4571  SelectionDAG &DAG) const;
4572 
4573  /// This callback is invoked for operations that are unsupported by the
4574  /// target, which are registered to use 'custom' lowering, and whose defined
4575  /// values are all legal. If the target has no operations that require custom
4576  /// lowering, it need not implement this. The default implementation of this
4577  /// aborts.
4578  virtual SDValue LowerOperation(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const;
4579 
4580  /// This callback is invoked when a node result type is illegal for the
4581  /// target, and the operation was registered to use 'custom' lowering for that
4582  /// result type. The target places new result values for the node in Results
4583  /// (their number and types must exactly match those of the original return
4584  /// values of the node), or leaves Results empty, which indicates that the
4585  /// node is not to be custom lowered after all.
4586  ///
4587  /// If the target has no operations that require custom lowering, it need not
4588  /// implement this. The default implementation aborts.
4589  virtual void ReplaceNodeResults(SDNode * /*N*/,
4590  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &/*Results*/,
4591  SelectionDAG &/*DAG*/) const {
4592  llvm_unreachable("ReplaceNodeResults not implemented for this target!");
4593  }

4620  enum ConstraintType {
4621  C_Register, // Constraint represents specific register(s).
4622  C_RegisterClass, // Constraint represents any of register(s) in class.
4623  C_Memory, // Memory constraint.
4624  C_Address, // Address constraint.
4625  C_Immediate, // Requires an immediate.
4626  C_Other, // Something else.
4627  C_Unknown // Unsupported constraint.
4628  };
4629 
4630  enum ConstraintWeight {
4631  // Generic weights.
4632  CW_Invalid = -1, // No match.
4633  CW_Okay = 0, // Acceptable.
4634  CW_Good = 1, // Good weight.
4635  CW_Better = 2, // Better weight.
4636  CW_Best = 3, // Best weight.
4637 
4638  // Well-known weights.
4639  CW_SpecificReg = CW_Okay, // Specific register operands.
4640  CW_Register = CW_Good, // Register operands.
4641  CW_Memory = CW_Better, // Memory operands.
4642  CW_Constant = CW_Best, // Constant operand.
4643  CW_Default = CW_Okay // Default or don't know type.
4644  };
4645 
4646  /// This contains information for each constraint that we are lowering.
4647  struct AsmOperandInfo : public InlineAsm::ConstraintInfo {
4648  /// This contains the actual string for the code, like "m". TargetLowering
4649  /// picks the 'best' code from ConstraintInfo::Codes that most closely
4650  /// matches the operand.
4651  std::string ConstraintCode;
4652 
4653  /// Information about the constraint code, e.g. Register, RegisterClass,
4654  /// Memory, Other, Unknown.
4655  TargetLowering::ConstraintType ConstraintType = TargetLowering::C_Unknown;
4656 
4657  /// If this is the result output operand or a clobber, this is null,
4658  /// otherwise it is the incoming operand to the CallInst. This gets
4659  /// modified as the asm is processed.
4660  Value *CallOperandVal = nullptr;
4661 
4662  /// The ValueType for the operand value.
4663  MVT ConstraintVT = MVT::Other;
4664 
4665  /// Copy constructor for copying from a ConstraintInfo.
4666  AsmOperandInfo(InlineAsm::ConstraintInfo Info)
4667  : InlineAsm::ConstraintInfo(std::move(Info)) {}
4668 
4669  /// Return true of this is an input operand that is a matching constraint
4670  /// like "4".
4671  bool isMatchingInputConstraint() const;
4672 
4673  /// If this is an input matching constraint, this method returns the output
4674  /// operand it matches.
4675  unsigned getMatchedOperand() const;
4676  };

4709  /// Given a physical register constraint (e.g. {edx}), return the register
4710  /// number and the register class for the register.
4711  ///
4712  /// Given a register class constraint, like 'r', if this corresponds directly
4713  /// to an LLVM register class, return a register of 0 and the register class
4714  /// pointer.
4715  ///
4716  /// This should only be used for C_Register constraints. On error, this
4717  /// returns a register number of 0 and a null register class pointer.

4722  virtual unsigned getInlineAsmMemConstraint(StringRef ConstraintCode) const {
4723  if (ConstraintCode == "m")
4724  return InlineAsm::Constraint_m;
4725  if (ConstraintCode == "o")
4726  return InlineAsm::Constraint_o;
4727  if (ConstraintCode == "X")
4728  return InlineAsm::Constraint_X;
4729  if (ConstraintCode == "p")
4730  return InlineAsm::Constraint_p;
4731  return InlineAsm::Constraint_Unknown;
4732  }

4790  /// Hooks for building estimates in place of slower divisions and square

4792 
4793  /// Return either a square root or its reciprocal estimate value for the input
4794  /// operand.
4795  /// \p Enabled is a ReciprocalEstimate enum with value either 'Unspecified' or
4796  /// 'Enabled' as set by a potential default override attribute.
4797  /// If \p RefinementSteps is 'Unspecified', the number of Newton-Raphson
4798  /// refinement iterations required to generate a sufficient (though not
4799  /// necessarily IEEE-754 compliant) estimate is returned in that parameter.
4800  /// The boolean UseOneConstNR output is used to select a Newton-Raphson
4801  /// algorithm implementation that uses either one or two constants.
4802  /// The boolean Reciprocal is used to select whether the estimate is for the
4803  /// square root of the input operand or the reciprocal of its square root.
4804  /// A target may choose to implement its own refinement within this function.
4805  /// If that's true, then return '0' as the number of RefinementSteps to avoid
4806  /// any further refinement of the estimate.
4807  /// An empty SDValue return means no estimate sequence can be created.
4808  virtual SDValue getSqrtEstimate(SDValue Operand, SelectionDAG &DAG,
4809  int Enabled, int &RefinementSteps,
4810  bool &UseOneConstNR, bool Reciprocal) const {
4811  return SDValue();
4812  }

4815  /// required for correctness since InstCombine might have canonicalized a
4816  /// fcmp+select sequence to a FMINNUM/FMAXNUM intrinsic. If we were to fall
4817  /// through to the default expansion/soften to libcall, we might introduce a
4818  /// link-time dependency on libm into a file that originally did not have one.
4819  SDValue createSelectForFMINNUM_FMAXNUM(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG) const;

5132  /// Legalize a SETCC or VP_SETCC with given LHS and RHS and condition code CC
5133  /// on the current target. A VP_SETCC will additionally be given a Mask
5134  /// and/or EVL not equal to SDValue().
5135  ///
5136  /// If the SETCC has been legalized using AND / OR, then the legalized node
5137  /// will be stored in LHS. RHS and CC will be set to SDValue(). NeedInvert
5138  /// will be set to false. This will also hold if the VP_SETCC has been
5139  /// legalized using VP_AND / VP_OR.
5140  ///
5141  /// If the SETCC / VP_SETCC has been legalized by using
5142  /// getSetCCSwappedOperands(), then the values of LHS and RHS will be
5143  /// swapped, CC will be set to the new condition, and NeedInvert will be set
5144  /// to false.
5145  ///
5146  /// If the SETCC / VP_SETCC has been legalized using the inverse condcode,
5147  /// then LHS and RHS will be unchanged, CC will set to the inverted condcode,
5148  /// and NeedInvert will be set to true. The caller must invert the result of
5149  /// the SETCC with SelectionDAG::getLogicalNOT() or take equivalent action to
5150  /// swap the effect of a true/false result.
5151  ///
5152  /// \returns true if the SETCC / VP_SETCC has been legalized, false if it
5153  /// hasn't.
5154  bool LegalizeSetCCCondCode(SelectionDAG &DAG, EVT VT, SDValue &LHS,
5155  SDValue &RHS, SDValue &CC, SDValue Mask,
5156  SDValue EVL, bool &NeedInvert, const SDLoc &dl,
5157  SDValue &Chain, bool IsSignaling = false) const;
5158 
5159  //===--------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5160  // Instruction Emitting Hooks
5161  //
5162 
5163  /// This method should be implemented by targets that mark instructions with
5164  /// the 'usesCustomInserter' flag. These instructions are special in various
5165  /// ways, which require special support to insert. The specified MachineInstr
5166  /// is created but not inserted into any basic blocks, and this method is
5167  /// called to expand it into a sequence of instructions, potentially also
5168  /// creating new basic blocks and control flow.
5169  /// As long as the returned basic block is different (i.e., we created a new
5170  /// one), the custom inserter is free to modify the rest of \p MBB.
5171  virtual MachineBasicBlock *
5172  EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const;
5173 
5174  /// This method should be implemented by targets that mark instructions with
5175  /// the 'hasPostISelHook' flag. These instructions must be adjusted after
5176  /// instruction selection by target hooks. e.g. To fill in optional defs for
5177  /// ARM 's' setting instructions.
5178  virtual void AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
5179  SDNode *Node) const;
